```

The Clientela API uses tokens to authenticate requests. Your token carries many privileges, so **be sure to keep it secure!** Do not share it or expose it on publicly available areas such as GitHub or client-side code.

<br />

**This endpoint accepts the following parameters:**

Parameter | Description | In
------------- | ------- | ------
`username`      | Your Admetricks username | Querystring
`password`      | Your Admetricks username | Querystring
`client_id`     | Clientela-specific key. The value is always the same for everyone | Querystring
`client_secret` | Clientela-specific secret. The value is always the same for everyone | Querystring

The values for client ID and client secret are:

- **Client ID:** `IW8M80h7qgCaSz4hPm3gr3wJP89NiJTPyhkwPurT`
- **Client Secret:** `KnBW84uyHlxwlNrKOXyym6Ro1IT6IlYdhScdop63hHddCzJIxUwDG7VItNgEONb1U2ebEH6fBmkYgX9LrZD4uqFJlYscHYn9MLxOm2qVccNE2WGEuePpKA7t3jQ2CvMu`

<br />

The authentication endpoint uses the following response/error codes:

<br />

Response code | Meaning
------------- | -------
200           | OK
401           | Invalid credentials
404           | Service not available
405           | Invalid method (i.e. `GET` instead of `POST`)
